# Data Safety

## Never Modify Real Data Without Consent

**Do not** write tests or code that modifies real data without explicit permission:

- ❌ Don't modify, delete, or publish real content records
- ❌ Don't modify database records
- ❌ Don't send real emails or notifications
- ❌ Don't mutate any external service data (CMS, APIs, etc.)

## Ask Before Testing With Real Data

When writing integration tests that could modify data:

1. Ask user how they want to handle test data
2. Suggest safe alternatives (test labels, env vars, separate test account)
3. Only proceed after getting explicit approval

## Use Test Data

- Use dedicated test messages/records
- Store test IDs in env vars or config
- Create special labels/filters to identify test data
- Never assume any real data is safe to modify
